<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/240.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 1, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President says that the British Government flatly refused the request
                            of the Guatemalan Chargé d’Affaires at London for time and stated that
                            they would insist upon the restoration of the coffee tax regardless of
                            any arrangement between the Guatemalan Government and the bankers.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>